Certainly! Sure! Sure! To write an if/then statement in C programming, you typically use the following syntax:

if (condition) {
  // Code to execute if the condition is true
} else {
  // Code to execute if the condition is false
}

For example, consider the following if/then statement:

if (age >= 18) {
  // Code to execute if the age is 18 or above
} else {
  // Code to execute if the age is below 18
}

In this example, if the condition (age >= 18) is true, the code within the first block will be executed. If the condition is false, the code within the else block will be executed.

